doctor - audit ReMinux health
Executable: /bin/doctor.sh
Alias: doctor

DESCRIPTION
  Checks the core ReMinux
  filesystem layout and
  important configuration
  and CC: Tweaked runtime
  compatibility.
  It reports missing files,
  risky local-auth settings
  broken UI/network
  combinations, disabled
  HTTP support and missing
  tab/window APIs.

USAGE
  doctor
  doctor --repair
  doctor help|-h|--help|?

OPTIONS
  --repair
    Recreates missing core
    files and directories,
    restores missing default
    settings and applies safe
    fallback values for known
    broken configurations.

NOTES
  doctor does not create a
  missing root password for
  local login. If the local
  root account file is gone,
  the next boot sanity check
  will prompt for a new one.
  It also reports optional
  CC: Tweaked features such
  as HTTP and shell tabs so
  compatibility problems can
  be diagnosed quickly.

SEE ALSO
  config
  top
